ont color=#333333>(1/31/02 2:35:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Problem #1: AFK Experience with Epic Pet</span><hr size=1> If we want intelligent fixes, we must accept the fact that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sees <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>over-powered</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> and deal with it.  I have come to the conclusion that this is mostly because <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, under most circumstances, have an adequate second character.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> believes that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are over-powered, and in particular the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> community disagrees, and a significant number insist that pet power should be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>increased</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> in order to perform adequately at the upper levels, and especially in raids.<br>
<br>
After some thought, I have concluded that as long as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can get experience by summoning their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and then going <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by a spawn, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>never</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> increase the power of pets in any meaningful way.  Under those circumstances, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would be fools to do so, as it would only increase the effectiveness of this exploit.  As long as the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> remains capped at its current utility, all other pets will remain capped.<br>
<br>
To remove this cap, and allow room for pet improvements, we must first eliminate this exploit.<br>
<br>
And it is our responsibility to come up with a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>fair and rational solution</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  Other wise we can expect <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to provide a poorly thought out <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;fix&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> which will have numerous unintended consequences, which will mostly likely negatively impact <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
What are the possible solutions?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Indifferent Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A very popular solution among <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, especially as it would dramatically ease the consequences of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> bad pathing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Reduces the consequences of bad pathing at a single stroke, would satisfy a large number of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, is easily coded.<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Enormous scope: dramatically alters game play and game balance almost certainly with numerous unintended consequences, a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pandora's Box</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: impossible to close once opened, may not solve AFK problem if <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can still arrange aggro <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (for example, by standing on or near spawn point)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Session Time-Out:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Have the server automatically disconnect after 60 minutes of inactivity <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (i.e no communications from the client)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Limited in scope, easily coded, mostly only effects the problem at hand, few unintended consequences, easily adjusted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Easily hacked, either in software or by putting a weight on top of the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>1</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> key which is bound to a server side social, such as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /who all Magician 60</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Absolute Time Limit on Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Pets die after one hour.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Easy to code, eliminates problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Would be seen as the ultimate <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> nerf</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, rioting in the streets, the end of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> class, would have many additional unintended consequences for any remaining <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Time Limit on Unattended Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Pets cast a self-buff called <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mortality</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which lasts one hour, and is over-ridden by any form of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burn out</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mortality</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ever expires without being over ridden, the pet poofs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Much more limited in scope than an absolute time limit, by and large only affects AFK pets.  Easily coded, does not effect legitimate tactics, much more difficult to hack<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantage:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Assumes there are little or no legitimate reasons to be AFK with a pet more than an hour, may yet be hackable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Note:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Use of social keys bound to number keys may make it impossible to distinguish AFK players, making timer variants trivial to bypass.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> DOAC Style anti-camping code:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Have subsequent spawns off the same point be reduced in experience value if the previous spawn was recently killed.  Alternately, have subsequent spawns at the same point increase in toughness without increasing the experience gained.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Reduces the value of camping static spawns, or pulling from known paths.  AFK experience would yeild diminishing returns, or in the case of increasingly stronger spawns, would result in the death of the AFKer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> enormous coding effort, numerous unintended consequences, would dramatically effect game play, would engender enormous customer resistance.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Nerf Unattended Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Make unbuffed pets weaker, so they are unable to solo experience yielding mobs without intervention.  To balance, increase the potency of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> dramatically, and/or add new pet buffs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Advantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Relatively easy to code, numbers can be adjusted after introduction, not as easily hacked, allows for over all increase of pet utility through new and improved buffs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Disadvantages:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Difficulty choosing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;correct&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> numbers, customer resistance, reduces utility of pet chaining <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (which is a central tactic of Magicians)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, maybe hackable through hotkeys anyway to allow for unattended exping.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Random Pet Poofing:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> See <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Absolute Timer On Pets</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> above.  Worse, because the flawed nature of the Random Number Generator.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Eliminate or replace Epic Pet:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The ultimate nerf, rioting in the streets, loss of customers, end of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> class, does not solve pet utility problem for remaining <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
These are all the proposals I recall reading or can think of at this time.  As proposed, they are all either have dramatic consequences, are possibly hackable, or would alienate the customer base.<br>
<br>
We must come up with a better solution <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>before</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;fixes&quot; it themselves.<br>
<br>
And, should we come to some kind of consensus as to a valid solution, we must make a convincing argument for it.<br>
<br>
